      "message": "Ok, I\u0027ll try to add it.\n\nOne issue I forgot about is closing the read transaction. I think it\u0027s going to be:\n\n  ctx, close :\u003d span.ReadOnlyTransaction(ctx)\n  defer close()\n\nWhich looks very much like regular context cancelation which some people tend to ignore :( Asking to do \n\n  ctx :\u003d span.ReadOnlyTransaction(ctx)\n  defer span.RO(ctx).Close()\n\nIs also kind of weird, but maybe better than `defer close()`?",
